step 1.Create a VM in GCP
 option 1:create vm manully (Go to GCP Console → Compute Engine → VM Instances → Create Instance.)
 option 2 : create vm using terraform

Step 2: after create vm , login into SSH

Step 3: Install GitLab Runner on the Vm

# Update packages
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install dependencies
sudo apt install -y curl git software-properties-common

# Install Docker
sudo apt install -y docker.io
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker

# Add GitLab Runner repo and install
curl -L https://packages.gitlab.com/install/repositories/runner/gitlab-runner/script.deb.sh | sudo bash

sudo apt install gitlab-runner -y
gitlab-runner --version

Step 4: Register the Runner

Go to GitLab Project → Settings → CI/CD → Runners → Registration token.

On VM:

sudo gitlab-runner register


GitLab URL: 

Token: <project registration token>

Description: GCP Runner

Tags: gcp,docker (optional)

Executor: docker

Default Docker image: ubuntu:22.04

Step 5: Start and Enable Runner
sudo systemctl enable gitlab-runner
sudo systemctl start gitlab-runner
sudo gitlab-runner status

